{:metadata {:description [{"text" "<p>This entry includes SERRATE (SE) from plants and its homologues, Ars2, from animals and Pir2 from Schizosaccharomyces pombe [[cite:PUB00094572]]. These proteins play a role in nuclear RNA metabolism. They interact with the nuclear cap-binding complex (CBC) and mediates interactions with diverse RNA processing and transport machineries in a transcript-dependent manner. Interestingly, the plant SERRATE does not have the RNA recognition motif (RRM) domain found in metazoans and S. pombe [[cite:PUB00090022]].</p>\n\n<p>In Arabidopsis, SE acts as a mediator between the cap-binding complex (CBC) and both the pre-mRNA splicing and primary microRNAs (miRNAs) processing machinery [[cite:PUB00090020], [cite:PUB00090021]]. Drosophila Ars2 has been shown to regulate both miRNA- and siRNA- dependent silencing and suppress RNA virus infection [[cite:PUB00063082]].</p>", "llm" false, "checked" false, "updated" false}], :is-reviewed-llm false, :representative-structure nil, :overlaps-with nil, :member-databases {"panther" {"PTHR13165" "ARSENITE-RESISTANCE PROTEIN 2"}}, :is-updated-llm false, :name {"name" "SERRATE/Ars2", "short" "SE/Ars2"}, :wikipedia nil, :source-database "interpro", :type "family", :counters {"structures" 7, "domain_architectures" 0, "proteomes" 1724, "taxa" 6619, "subfamilies" 0, "interactions" 0, "matches" 4907, "sets" 0, "proteins" 4907, "structural_models" {"alphafold" 3024}, "pathways" 12}, :integrated nil, :cross-references {}, :set-info nil, :accession "IPR039727", :literature {"PUB00094572" {"URL" nil, "issue" "6", "authors" ["Egan ED" "Braun CR" "Gygi SP" "Moazed D."], "ISO_journal" "RNA", "DOI_URL" nil, "medline_journal" "RNA", "title" "Post-transcriptional regulation of meiotic genes by a nuclear RNA silencing complex.", "year" 2014, "raw_pages" "867-81", "volume" "20", "ISBN" nil, "PMID" 24713849}, "PUB00090020" {"URL" nil, "issue" "25", "authors" ["Laubinger S" "Sachsenberg T" "Zeller G" "Busch W" "Lohmann JU" "R